HEADWORD: September
<hw>Sep*tem"ber</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>septem</ets> seven, as being the seventh month of the Roman year,
which began with March: cf. F. <ets>septembre</ets>. See
<er>Seven</er>.]</ety> <def>The ninth month of the year, containing
thurty days.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

